originalText.text: Please consider this a friendly advice to refrain from making purchases through this platform. Once your payment is processed, an unsettling period of inactivity ensues, which could last a week or sometimes even two. During this time, expect no shipment of your order. Despite lodging complaints and sending emails, your efforts to garner a response may remain futile. Furthermore, should you wish to return the item or cancel the order within this timeframe, it is regrettably impossible.

originalText.text: Ordered a fridge through them, with line items spelling out the purchase price and shipping fees to a total of 2800. They came back a week later saying "system mistake" and that the actual price for the fridge was 2800 and now the new shipping fees added on would equate to a total price of 3100. Meanwhile Lowe's has price mistakes and honors them, not leaving the consumer out to dry when they're expecting a critical appliance to show up. Waste of time.
